159
00:06:16,506 --> 00:06:17,840
- Make it an eel.
- Okay.

160
00:06:17,882 --> 00:06:19,801
- It's gonna be an eel!
- Better.

161
00:06:19,842 --> 00:06:22,887
<i>But alone with Buster,</i>
<i>the tension grew worse,</i>

162
00:06:22,929 --> 00:06:26,682
<i>and things came to a head</i>
<i>the night before the trial.</i>

163
00:06:26,724 --> 00:06:28,268
Buster, I'm going to exhale!

164
00:06:28,310 --> 00:06:29,894
No, please!

165
00:06:29,936 --> 00:06:32,688
I've had, like, seven
in the past half hour.

166
00:06:32,730 --> 00:06:35,317
You're not the one
staring five years in the face.

167
00:06:35,358 --> 00:06:38,278
Well, right now, I'm staring at
a hundred years in the face!

168
00:06:38,320 --> 00:06:40,113
(whispers):
How dare you.

169
00:06:40,155 --> 00:06:43,492
Would you mind?

170
00:06:43,533 --> 00:06:45,701
Be careful, defendant.

171
00:06:45,743 --> 00:06:48,579
Remember who you're talking to.

172
00:06:48,621 --> 00:06:50,832
